# Docker Compose Env File Rule

When running Docker Compose commands in this repository, always use `.env.local`.

- For start/stop/restart/status/logs/config commands, prefer:
  - `docker compose --env-file .env.local up ...`
  - `docker compose --env-file .env.local down ...`
  - `docker compose --env-file .env.local ps`
  - `docker compose --env-file .env.local logs ...`
  - `docker compose --env-file .env.local config`
- Run commands from the repo root: `/home/justin-p/_git/github/testing`.
- Do not assume `.env` is the desired source for local development credentials.
- If a command was run without `--env-file .env.local`, rerun it with the flag.
